                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-95" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-95" type="given" value="SARAH ANN"></interp>SARAH ANN ROBERTS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at 21, King's Road, Peckham—I am acquainted with the prisoner Langley—this is my pass-book—on 30th July and 1st August, 1874, I paid 300<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. in notes into my account, which I received from Dr. Langley as a present—on 4th August, 1874, I drew a cheque to Mr. Langley for 210<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., which is destroyed—I do not keep any cheques—on 8th January, 1875, I drew another cheque for 230<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., and gave it to Dr. Langley as a present—I did not owe him any money—on 2nd November, 1874, I paid 100<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. into my account—I suppose it was received from Langley.</p>
